Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{700%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the @Central American Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%g}.

Heat a large #saucepan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @Diced Chorizo{90%g} and fry until it starts to brown, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once the chorizo is browned, stir in the @Mixed Beans{1%carton} along with their liquid, @Finely Chopped Tomatoes with Onion and Garlic{½%carton}, @Red Wine Stock Paste{28%g}, @Chipotle Paste{20%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and the @Sugar{1%tsp} for the sauce.

Bring the chorizo chilli to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Once the chilli has thickened, stir in the @Butter{20%g} until melted.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Add a splash of @water{} if you feel it needs it.

Share the potato wedges between your serving #bowls{}.

Top with the chorizo chipotle chilli.

Drizzle over the @Soured Cream{75%g} and sprinkle over the cheese to finish.

Enjoy!